The paper also discusses the use of deep learning for this task, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of theory and methods for processing rotations, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks for motion estimation, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the processing of 3D data, which makes cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category.
